FBIS3-4943 "dreas042_h_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-042 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Mar 1994 Brunei, Malaysia & Singapore Malaysia Reaction to UK Press Allegations Continues Defense Minister on British Frigates BK0303092494 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0600 GMT 3 Mar 94 BK0303092494 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Defense Minister Datuk Sri Najib Tun Razak said the purchase of the Royal Malaysian Navy's frigates worth 1.2 billion ringgit from a British company was a genuine value-for-money buy. Denying an allegation that the government had been ripped off by the company Yarrow Shipbuilders, he said as far as the armed forces was concerned, the purchase was within the requirement. He said the contractor had quoted a figure of 1.4 billion ringgit, which was in line with the minister's evaluation of the market value. The proposed purchase included the weaponry systems fitted on the ship, which was almost equivalent to the type (Silver Creek) frigate, a bigger class frigate (?acquired) by Malaysia. When the contract was signed, the pound sterling was at 3.7 against the ringgit. Datuk Sri Najib said he had no (?clues) to seek legal action on the allegation made by the British opposition MP Stephen Byers, that Yarrow had ripped off the government. He was speaking to reporters after the ministry's [words indistinct] in Kuala Lumpur.
